## 9. Security Considerations

Path traversal
  The VFS router normalizes every incoming path against the session's mount
  root before any lookup. Paths containing ".." components after normalization
  are rejected with EPERM.

Symlink attacks
  Symlinks within the git tree are followed only within the virtual root.
  A symlink pointing outside /vdev/<session-id>/ is served as a broken link.

Session isolation
  Each session directory is accessible only to the UID that created it
  (mode 700, FUSE allow_root=false). The control socket is mode 600, owned
  by the simgit user/group.

Delta store integrity
  Blob filenames are SHA-256 hashes of content. Any blob whose filename does
  not match its content hash is rejected on read (silent corruption detection).

Denial of service
  Max open sessions: configurable (default 256).
  Max delta size per session: configurable (default 2 GB).
  Max lock TTL: configurable (default 1 hour).
  These limits are enforced at session.create and write time.

Git object store reads
  simgitd opens the git repo read-only. It never calls git write operations
  on the base repo; all writes go to the delta store. The flatten/commit
  operation creates new objects but does not modify existing ones (git's
  immutable object model guarantees this).


