                                     select at init time with --vfs-backend flag.

  FUSE performance overhead vs. disk Blob LRU cache in daemon; Phase 7 option
                                     to use in-kernel OverlayFS on Linux.

  Large binary files flooding delta  Per-session delta size limit (§9).
  store                              Warn at 80% threshold; block at 100%.

  Daemon crash loses active sessions SQLite WAL gives durability; FUSE mounts
                                     are re-attached on restart (Phase 2).

  gix API instability (pre-1.0)      Pin to a specific gix version; wrap in
                                     an internal trait so the backend is
                                     swappable if needed.

  Agent holding write lock forever   TTL sweeper (Phase 3) forcibly releases
                                     locks after configurable timeout.

  Conflicting flattens               Pre-commit conflict check (Phase 4);
                                     three-way auto-merge as best-effort;
                                     human review required on true conflicts.


## 11. Success Metrics

  Metric                              Target
  ----------------------------------  -------------------------
  Session creation latency            < 5 ms
  FUSE read throughput (warm cache)   ≥ 200 MB/s
  FUSE write throughput               ≥ 100 MB/s
  Lock acquire latency                < 1 ms
  Flatten (commit) latency, 500 files < 500 ms
  Max concurrent sessions             ≥ 256 on a 16-core host
  Zero-copy session creation          0 MB disk (baseline only)
  Borrow false-positive rate          0% (different-path writes)
  Data loss on daemon SIGKILL         0 bytes (WAL + crash recovery)


